name: Jewellery Quarter Planters
short_description: Community herbs in urban street planters.
description: Incredible Edible JQ project provides free rosemary, thyme, and mint in raised beds.

name: Cannon Hill Park Orchard
description: Publicly accessible fruit trees located near the MAC center. Please pick only what you need.

name: Sutton Park Hazels
description: Extensive hazel groves found near the Holly Hurst area of the park.

name: Digbeth Canal Sea Beet
short_description: Wild greens growing along the canal towpath.
description: Hardy greens found along the Grand Union Canal towpath near Fazeley St.

name: Lickey Hills Bilberries
description: Low-growing berries found across the heathland areas of the Lickey Hills.

name: Moseley Bog Wild Garlic
description: Massive carpets of wild garlic available in the spring. Follow the boardwalks.

name: Stirchley Fruit Trail
short_description: Urban fruit path with berries and plums.
description: Part of the Stirchley 'Incredible Edible' route along the Rea Valley Path.

name: Bournville Walnut Trees
description: Scattered walnut trees found in the parkland around the Cadbury factory.

name: Handsworth Park Elder
description: Large elder shrubs line the perimeter of the lake and cricket pitch.

name: Cotteridge Park Orchard
description: Managed by Friends of Cotteridge Park. Open for local harvesting.

name: Woodgate Valley Sloes
description: Ideal for gin-making; found in the hedgerows near the visitor center.

name: Kings Heath Park Herbs
description: The demonstration gardens often have excess herbs marked for public picking.

name: Castle Bromwich Sloes
description: Traditional hedgerows around the historic gardens offer sloes and hips.

name: Edgbaston Reservoir Berries
description: High-yield blackberry brambles surround the 2.8km circular path.

name: Clent Hills Sweet Chestnut
description: Found on the lower slopes near the Nimmings Wood car park.
